Back in 2012, I posted this photo as my first ever ‚Äúfitspo‚Äù post on social media - to share with the world my new found *innocent* ‚Äúpassion‚Äù for health and fitness.. üòÖ
.

.

Dieting, meal plans, fitness competitions, 30 day challenges, detox‚Äôs ‚Äî they never told me I‚Äôd lose my period, lose my hair, lose my personality/identity, my freedom, my digestion, my metabolism, my satiety, my sanity, my sleep.. .

no one ever talks about the bad things that could happen from just restricting a bit here and there..

But I kept pushing ‚Äî cutting more and more foods, and exercising more and more.. hating myself and my body..nothing was ever good enough..
.

I soon started to feel crazy around food.. I could no longer maintain my "willpower" for longer than a week..

.

Of course I have no regrets..it‚Äôs all taught me so much..

But what I DO HAVE, is a burning passion to now spread awareness about the dysfunction within the health and fitness industry, so others don‚Äôt have to learn in this horrific way I, and thousands of other women and men, all to often have been *accidentally* learning.. .

.

I realized why, what I was doing the whole time, no matter what I tried, was only making things worse..
.
.

Diets don‚Äôt work, they never will.
.

.
.
Read more about my story and what you can do in my book ‚Äúdamn the diets‚Äù
.

BINEGING // EXTREME HUNGER // ‚ÄúBOTTOMLESS PIT HUNGER‚Äù..
.
.

These are the inevitable results from restriction and deprivation of calories, food groups or macronutrients of any kind.
.
.

Feast always follows Famine - Bingeing always follows deprivation. It‚Äôs simply the physiological response to starvation (also known as a caloric deficit) .
.

Extreme and ‚Äúuncontrollable‚Äù hunger works as a survival mechanism to keep you alive and thriving! It‚Äôs a cry for help as the body is suffering badly!
.
.

Your body feels it‚Äôs survival is being threatened when restricted in ANY way. It senses a famine - a lack of food, so it kicks into survival mode, which then leads to lowering the metabolism in efforts to burn the least amount of energy possible and then the conservation and holding onto anything that  does come in. This is to prepare for the future famine. - also known as post-diet- weight-regain and overshoot,  compared to your weight just prior to ever dieting or restricting.
.
.

Don‚Äôt fear your hunger. Your hunger is there for a reason and your body knows what it‚Äôs doing! It knows more than we ‚Äúthink‚Äù we know! Our body is not trying to deceive us.
.
.

LISTEN. Your hunger cues are nonverbal communication tools the body uses to communicate its needs, when it needs it, what it needs and how much it needs (satiety signals).
.
.

The longer you continue the cycle of restrict-over exercise-binge cycle, the further you push yourself away from freedom and TRUE health and fitness. The sicker you‚Äôll get, the more unhappy you‚Äôll feel, the more nothing will ever be good enough and the stronger the hunger will be!
.
.
Just eat the damn food without guilt, shame or fear!
.
.

What‚Äôs more fulfilling at the end of the day?
.

Seems like a no brainer right? But for some it‚Äôs far more complicated and not that easy to just pick one..
